latestPosts.caption:
Shaving 101 (for the ladies!) 🫧 
Let’s break the myth: shaving your face does not make your hair grow back thicker or darker. It’s actually one of the best-kept secrets for smoother skin, better product absorption and flawless makeup application

Here’s the tea:
- Use a clean, single-blade facial razor
- Always shave on clean skin with a bit of facial oil for some slip
- Light, downward strokes only - no pressure needed
- Follow with a calming, hydrating serum/moisturiser 

Have you tried it yet or are you still on the fence?

#ShavingMythBusted #FaceShavingForWomen #SkinPrepEssentials #GlassySkinSteps #smoothskin #skincaretips

latestPosts.caption:
This combo is such a game changer!! Emolene and @paulaschoice 10% Azelaic Acid booster work so well when used together and the results are just 💯 

+ Gets rid of clogged pores/tiny bumps
+ Improved skin texture
+ Skin feels so soft and supple
+ Helps maintain a healthy skin barrier and restores moisture 

How I like to use it
I use it at night on cleansed skin. Either spot treat with the azelaic acid and follow it up with emolene OR
Mix the two together and use it at once all over

Skincare is subjective and this is something that works for me. Pls do a patch test if you’re unsure

Always my first stop in Paris 🇫🇷 Here’s what you should get ⬇️

+ @larocheposay Body Cream - so good for extremely dry skin
+ La Roche Posay Anthelios UV Fluide Invisible - spf 50+ no white cast and super lightweight
+ La Roche Posay Lipikar shower gel - very gentle and perfect for sensitive skin
+ @avene Hydrance Legere hydrating cream - no fuss moisturiser and I actually prefer this to the LRP cicaplast 
+ @caudalie thé des vignes hyaluronic nourishing body lotion - I love this one. You get a massive size for 18eur which is amazing 
+ Caudalie Vinopure purifying cleansing gel - got this for Parth - amazing for oily/combo skin
+ @eucerin Aquaphor healing ointment - the BEST multi purpose ointment for chapped lips, elbows, knees 
+ @nuxe Honey lip oil - honestly this doesn’t last very long but I still enjoy using it because of how light it is. Don’t forget to check the minis in the checkout aisle
